1 AN ACT concerning the state board of education; increasing compensation
2 of members of the board; establishing a daily rate of compensation that
3 corresponds to the daily rate of compensation for services rendered by
4 members of the legislature while in session; amending K.S.A. 72-253
5 and repealing the existing section.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 72-253 is hereby amended to read as follows: 72-
9 253. (a) The state board of education may authorize members thereof to
10 attend in-state meetings for participation in matters of educational interest
11 to the state of Kansas, and when attending a meeting so authorized,
12 members shall receive compensation and travel expenses and subsistence
13 expenses or allowances as provided in K.S.A. 75-3212, and amendments
14 thereto, for members of the legislature. Whenever under any provision of
15 law, a member of the state board of education is authorized to attend an
16 out-of-state meeting, or whenever the state board of education authorizes
17 one of its members to attend an out-of-state meeting for participation in
18 matters of educational interest to the state of Kansas such members, when
19 attending a meeting so authorized, shall receive compensation and travel
20 expenses and subsistence expenses as provided in K.S.A. 75-3212, and
21 amendments thereto, for members of the legislature.
22 (b) Notwithstanding the provisions of K.S.A. 46-137a and 75-3212,
23 and amendments thereto, when attending any such in-state or out-of-state
24 meeting authorized in accordance with subsection (a), members of the
25 state board of education shall receive compensation in an amount that
26 corresponds to the daily rate of compensation for services rendered by
27 members of the legislature while in session. For purposes of this section,
28 such daily rate of compensation for members of the state board shall be
29 determined as follows:
30 (1) Determine the base annual salary of members of the legislature
31 established by the legislative compensation commission pursuant to K.S.A.
32 46-3102, and amendments thereto, including any salary indexing
33 adjustments made to such base annual salary, and multiply such amount
34 by 0.6003; and
35 (2) divide the amount determined pursuant to paragraph (1) by 90.

